  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Analyst (Talend Data Integration & Informatica BDM)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>We are seeking a Data Integration Analyst to generate and operationalize insights from diverse data sources, supporting key stakeholders through comprehensive data lifecycle management and data supply chains. You will extract, normalize, and transform data to deliver actionable business and performance insights via dashboard visualizations.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Extract, normalize, and transform data from multiple sources to support business and performance insights</li><li>Build and maintain complex SQL queries and data pipelines to ensure reliable data flow and accessibility</li><li>Develop compelling and user-friendly data visualizations using commercial and/or open-source BI tools to communicate insights effectively</li><li>Code in Python, R, or similar scripting languages to operationalize analytics workflows and automate data processes</li><li>Collaborate with stakeholders to understand core business objectives and design end-to-end data-centric solutions that address their needs</li><li>Apply critical thinking and analytical problem-solving skills to identify data issues and optimize data integration processes</li><li>Maintain high attention to detail to ensure data accuracy and integrity throughout the data lifecycle</li><li>Continuously develop expertise within your area of responsibility by staying current with emerging market offerings and technologies</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Proficiency in SQL for building and maintaining complex queries and data pipelines</li><li>Experience building data visualizations and analytics using commercial and/or open-source BI tools</li><li>Coding capability in Python, R, or similar scripting languages to operationalize analytics workflows</li><li>Minimum 1-2 years of experience in data analysis and visualization</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Undergraduate or graduate degree in Computer Science or equivalent</li><li>Experience with Amazon Web Services, Cloudera, or other cloud services</li><li>Data pipeline and/or database development experience</li><li>Knowledge of statistical modeling, predictive analytics, or machine learning</li><li>Certification in leading data analytics platforms such as Tableau, Qlik, MicroStrategy, Informatica, Talend, Microsoft SAS, or IBM</li></ul><p>Work Location Depot Road</p>",
